He has enough paint to make a strip 25 meters long. We need to find the total area in square centimeters that this paint can cover. First, convert the length from meters to centimeters and the width from millimeters to centimeters: - 25 meters = 2500 centimeters - 6.5 millimeters = 0.65 centimeters Next, calculate the area by multiplying the length and width in centimeters: \[ 2500 \, \text{cm} \times 0.65 \, \text{cm} = 1625 \, \text{cm}^2 \] To verify, we can also convert all measurements to millimeters and then convert the result to square centimeters: - 25 meters = 25000 millimeters - Width = 6.5 millimeters Calculate the area in square millimeters: \[ 25000 \, \text{mm} \times 6.5 \, \text{mm} = 162500 \, \text{mm}^2 \] Convert square millimeters to square centimeters (1 cmÂ² = 100 mmÂ²): \[ 162500 \, \text{mm}^2 \div 100 = 1625 \, \text{cm}^2 \] Both methods confirm that the total area is: \[ \boxed{1625} \]
